            "body": "Continuing the TODO. MANUS-side blocker confirmed concrete + reproducible; VIVE-side scaffolded offline.\n\n== MANUS hardware E2E (still blocked) ==\n\nReproduced the libusb permission failure with hard evidence:\n- log:   ~/.claude/jobs/manus_vive/probe_segfault.log  sha256=d2715e96c542ff66cf6df2f9101b511110efe9af3ca29b1b204cfbc304bde2d7\n- cmd:   cd ~/workspace/manus_wrapper && python3 scripts/probe_dongle.py\n- exit:  139 (SIGSEGV) — libManusSDK_Integrated.so segfaults attempting libusb_open on /dev/bus/usb/003/013 (mode 0664 root:root, boris in plugdev but device not group-rw)\n- root cause: udev rule '99-manus-libusb.rules' (SUBSYSTEM==usb, ATTR{idVendor}==3325, MODE=0666) is not installed in /etc/udev/rules.d/; no system-managed alternative grants non-root access to vid 0x3325 devices.\n\nmanus_wrapper offline tests still PASS (26/26) so the wrapper code itself is healthy:\n- cd ~/workspace/manus_wrapper && python3 -m pytest tests/\n\n== VIVE Tracker scaffold (new artifact, offline-verifiable) ==\n\nNew sibling repo at ~/workspace/vive_wrapper/ (mirrors manus_wrapper / wuji_glove_wrapper layout).\n- Initial commit: 1aa1dd2aeb7a5ce3ac8058248f3a515771667f07 (root commit, 12 files, 886 insertions)\n- Author: boris <lv.robotics.lab@gmail.com>, no co-author trailer (per memory).\n\nStructure:\n  src/vive_wrapper/{tracker.py, config.py, cli.py, __init__.py}\n  scripts/{probe_module.py, list_trackers.py}\n  examples/openvr_input.yaml\n  tests/test_offline.py (10 tests)\n  docs/manus_vive_integration.md (unified MANUS+VIVE+camera+robot design)\n\nOpenVRTrackerWrapper is adapted from wuji-hand-teleop's openvr_input/openvr_tracker_wrapper.py with the ROS2 dependency stripped and explicit dual timestamps (CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW ns + UTC μs) added so it composes with wuji_glove_wrapper's UTC-μs time base. Coordinate-correction matrices (CHEST / LEFT_WRIST / RIGHT_WRIST) preserved BIT-EXACTLY from upstream — guarded by test_correction_matrices_bitwise_match_upstream so any existing retargeting recipe / recorded trajectory remains valid.\n\nVerifier runs (logs in ~/.claude/jobs/manus_vive/):\n- vive_tests.log              sha256=89e2eeda771e06ef84f59be6d2ee8d7f5ab5be6b7d3794c851cdfdbf82ef9077\n  cmd: cd ~/workspace/vive_wrapper && .venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/ -v\n  result: 10 passed in 0.09s\n- vive_probe.log              sha256=90320023804dfb3c2bb7cbebdc3c2aa13bba1e77d786d11eff8b5b87e89c74b6\n  cmd: .venv/bin/python scripts/probe_module.py\n  result: openvr 2.12.1401 loads, all 8 required symbols present (init, shutdown, VRSystem, VRApplication_Other, TrackedDeviceClass_GenericTracker, k_unMaxTrackedDeviceCount, Prop_SerialNumber_String, TrackingUniverseStanding)\n- vive_list_no_steamvr.log    sha256=591b2e3cfe46bc6561eb2fff865623890c4169c062f4eacfc32787d7454d80dd\n  cmd: .venv/bin/python scripts/list_trackers.py\n  result: clean ViveError 'openvr.init failed — is SteamVR running?' (concrete proof that wrapper fails-fast when SteamVR is not running, and that SteamVR is in fact not installed: ~/.steam, ~/.local/share/Steam both absent; no /etc/udev/rules.d/*vive* or SteamVR libraries on PATH)\n\nEnv: uv 0.11.7 venv with python 3.10.12, deps openvr==2.12.1401, numpy==2.2.6, pyyaml==6.0.3, pytest==9.0.3.\n\n== Unified integration design doc ==\n\ndocs/manus_vive_integration.md (sha256=5681c72388893beaf55ccff7db3ab6790a1a745ce4a0ea8b0e8e05edada63443) covers all four task-description deliverables on paper, ready to execute once hardware is unblocked:\n  1. Stream inventory + time-sync invariants (UTC μs join key, <1ms drift bound, 1s heartbeat markers)\n  2. Extrinsic calibration (T_world_vive via hand-eye AX=YB on Franka, T_wrist_manus_root via printed jig, T_world_camera reused from existing infra)\n  3. Recording format (per-stream Parquet keyed on wall_us, optional ros2 bag)\n  4. Retargeting validation (replay manus fingers -> wuji-retargeting, replay vive_wrist -> Franka EE, compare against franka_state; per-session report.html with p95 thresholds)\n\n== What I still need from a human (sudo bundle) ==\n\nBoth hardware paths require root. Single sudo session needed:\n\n  # (1) MANUS libusb access — replug dongle after\n  sudo cp ~/workspace/manus_wrapper/third_party/99-manus-libusb.rules /etc/udev/rules.d/99-manus-libusb.rules\n  sudo udevadm control --reload-rules && sudo udevadm trigger\n  # then physically unplug + replug the MANUS Pro dongle (3325:0049)\n\n  # (2) SteamVR install — needs Steam client first\n  # easiest path on Ubuntu 22.04:\n  sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y steam\n  # then run 'steam' as user boris, sign in, install 'SteamVR' from the Tools menu\n  # then in SteamVR pair each VIVE Tracker, note its LHR-XXXXXXXX serial\n\nAfter both: rerun the two verifiers above; the MANUS probe should report dongle id, and vive-list should print serial(s).\n\nStatus: leaving as needs_user/blocked (hardware + sudo required, not work I can do under this worker's policy). Concrete deliverables committed: vive_wrapper scaffold @ 1aa1dd2, integration design doc, four reproducible verifier logs with sha256.",
