            "body": "Update: udev blocker is resolved (local Codex host did the sudo install). Continued with non-hardware integration work; full MANUS+VIVE fusion adapter now implemented and offline-verified.\n\n== Resolved (no longer blocking) ==\n\n- udev rule installed: /etc/udev/rules.d/99-manus-libusb.rules present (lsof confirmed)\n- MANUS dongle now /dev/bus/usb/003/013 crw-rw-rw- (was 0664 root:root)\n- manus_wrapper/src/manus_wrapper/sdk.py patched by Codex:\n    * CoreSdk_SetRawSkeletonHandMotion moved POST CoreSdk_ConnectToHost (was segfaulting before)\n    * CoreSdk_GetNumberOfDongles / GetNumberOfAvailableGloves return [] on FunctionNotAvailable (CoreLite-host)\n- python3 scripts/probe_dongle.py: no more segfault. CoreLite starts all services cleanly (Callbacks, SkeletonService, Coordinator, Devices, Gestures, Calibration, Telemetry), library bridges HIDAPIBridge + EmbeddedBridge load, hot-plug callback thread starts. probe exits 2 only because dongle-enum API is FunctionNotAvailable on CoreLite — not a permission problem.\n- manus_wrapper pytest: 26/26 pass\n\nEvidence (sha256 in ~/.claude/jobs/manus_vive/):\n  probe_corelite_connect.log    4006572384f22b8d26e3060f162e0a0d4c2b1cb01df21dc06e8d7adcc05b5598\n  list_gloves.log               0f3c03c57f1302966a9de776d50fc3474017c679d1fb3769005199f864e13f95\n\n== New deliverable: vive_wrapper @ 979b19c9acaf4bfb08766e4b55359cf9d6458f78 ==\n\n~/workspace/vive_wrapper/ now has both the VIVE adapter AND the fused MANUS+VIVE composition layer described in the task. Two commits:\n  1aa1dd2 Initial scaffold for VIVE Tracker integration in MANUS+VIVE input stack\n  979b19c Add fused MANUS+VIVE adapter and offline demo\n\nNew module: vive_wrapper.fused (src/vive_wrapper/fused.py, sha256=4023ccc63d363f06faf74448c9e6b3d0f8338d1e5a154543710394ddb719096a)\n\n- HandWristCalibration(T_world_vive, T_wrist_manus_root): the two 4x4 transforms calibrated once per platform (see docs/manus_vive_integration.md §3).\n- fuse(side, manus_frame, wrist_frame, calibration, skew_max_us=50_000): pure function composing world ← T_world_vive @ T_vive_wrist @ T_wrist_manus_root, transforming MediaPipe-21 keypoints into world, enforcing a configurable skew bound, returning a FusedHandFrame{ side, keypoints_world, wrist_pose_world, wall_us, manus_wall_us, vive_wall_us, skew_us, valid, notes }.\n- ManusFrameLike / WristFrameLike: runtime-checkable Protocols. manus_wrapper.GloveFrame (with .to_mediapipe() and .publish_time_ns) plugs in without any import-time coupling.\n- StubManusFrame / StubWristFrame: lightweight stand-ins for CI + retargeting validation.\n\nTests (offline, no hardware, no SteamVR):\n  tests/test_fused.py    (sha256=77e1c0175b1a730a299b492f95e4763732c4260f6ff90245cf3547dc09346f50)\n  tests/test_offline.py  (sha256=1483ef417a8ea9abf522d815821a122bd541d451485aca624d5ae0a28f38e801)\n  Verifier run log: ~/.claude/jobs/manus_vive/vive_tests_v2.log sha256=66852f5df5d9a1128130a903d1471d80f7fbb83ae461303154f09a1198e1021b\n  Result: 22 passed in 0.14s\n  Coverage: identity passthrough, world translation, z-axis rotation, skew rejection (60ms > 50ms bound), skew acceptance (10ms within bound), max-wall-us aggregation, shape-mismatch reporting, Protocol recognition of stubs, error notes propagation.\n\nOffline E2E demo: examples/fused_demo.py\n  Verifier run log: ~/.claude/jobs/manus_vive/vive_fused_demo.log sha256=e0a64cf949b2f71cab9a9e2f4dc7f3a49f1755b85c530708b2574fd3c3ae3765\n  Asserts wrist world position = T_world_vive @ T_vive_wrist origin = (0.5, 1.0, 1.2). Pass.\n\nUpdated docs: docs/manus_vive_integration.md (sha256=874ed5358df13e1067f5fc72443bba6435055ece1c2cda0406a7c33857108a99) — design now references the actual code module + reflects current hw state.\n\n== Remaining (pure hardware, no sudo needed from a worker) ==\n\n1) MANUS glove actual streaming: power on the glove(s), pair with the dongle in the MANUS Core 3 desktop GUI (or wait for the dongle's pairing window). CoreLite host-level connect is already verified; once a glove appears the skeleton callback in manus_wrapper.sdk will produce frames. After that, examples/quickstart.py in manus_wrapper should print MediaPipe-21 keypoints.\n\n2) VIVE Tracker hardware path: needs Steam + SteamVR install (one-time), plus physical VIVE Tracker(s) + base station(s):\n   - install Steam: 'sudo apt install steam' (or .deb from store.steampowered.com)\n   - launch Steam → Tools → SteamVR → install\n   - plug in VIVE wireless dongle (Bluetooth-flavoured Valve dongle), power on tracker(s), pair in SteamVR's Devices menu, record the LHR-XXXXXXXX serials into examples/openvr_input.yaml\n   - then: cd ~/workspace/vive_wrapper && .venv/bin/python scripts/list_trackers.py — should list every paired tracker. Last verified failure (SteamVR not running) at ~/.claude/jobs/manus_vive/vive_list_no_steamvr.log sha=591b2e3cfe46bc6561eb2fff865623890c4169c062f4eacfc32787d7454d80dd.\n\n== Review artifact summary ==\n\nWorktree: /home/boris/workspace/vive_wrapper\nGit HEAD: 979b19c9acaf4bfb08766e4b55359cf9d6458f78  (branch master, 2 commits, 18 files, 1469 lines)\nTest verifier: .venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/ -v   → 22 passed\nDemo verifier: cd /home/boris/workspace/vive_wrapper && .venv/bin/python examples/fused_demo.py  → \"OK — wrist world position matches expected (0.5, 1.0, 1.2).\"\nCompanion MANUS side: /home/boris/workspace/manus_wrapper (uncommitted, but pytest 26/26 + probe connects to CoreLite cleanly).\n\nMoving status from blocked → review. The integration adapter, design doc, and offline verification cover the four task-description deliverables (time-sync, calibration, recording format, retargeting validation interfaces). Hardware-only follow-ups (glove power-on/pair, SteamVR install + tracker pair) are not blockers I can clear from this worker; they are the natural next milestone once hardware is in place.",
