            "body": "DREAMZERO FEASIBILITY (preliminary, before any GPU attempt):\n\nUpstream README dreamzero/README.md explicitly states:\n- 'Hardware: Multi-GPU setup (tested on GB200, H100)'\n- 'Minimum: 2 GPUs for distributed inference'\n- 'CUDA: Compatible GPU with CUDA 12.9+'\n- Inference invocation: 'python -m torch.distributed.run --standalone --nproc_per_node=2 socket_test_optimized_AR.py'\n- DiT inference latency: ~0.6s on GB200, ~3s on H100; no single-GPU baseline reported.\n\nBackbone is 14B params (Wan2.2-I2V). On bf16: weights alone ~28GB. Even with t5_cpu+vae_cpu offloading, single 32GB RTX 5090 cannot host the DiT for distributed inference because the upstream code requires nproc_per_node>=2 and dim-parallel sequence sharding. Without modifying the torchrun entrypoint to single-rank (which would also bypass the sequence-parallel layers), the server won't start.\n\nENV mismatch additional: dreamzero pyproject pins torch==2.8.0/torchvision==0.23.0 with cu129; wmfactory env is torch 2.9.0+cu128. Conflict resolvable with a separate env, but moot if hardware blocks anyway.\n\nCONCLUSION for DreamZero in 'worth entering training or modification?' framing:\n- Not testable as-published on this single-5090 box.\n- If access to multi-GPU box (>=2 H100 or 1 GB200): worth running; the model card claims #1 on MolmoSpaces + RoboArena, trained from scratch on DROID only.\n- Alternative: hosted API access via Google form https://forms.gle/zCj5zjDvHsoeuMXU7 (request needed) — could evaluate via sim-evals without local GPU. Mark needs_user if you want me to file that form OR provision a 2-GPU box.\n\nCtrl-World inference is feasible here (smaller SVD-based, will run after the 8.6G ckpt download finishes ~5min). Will follow with run results.",
