        "title": "Add ComPose-style object-pose QA",
        "description": "Use ComPose (arXiv:2605.23523) as the reference for upgrading hand-removal QA from mask-local pixel differences to object/contact trajectory checks. Treat hands in the raw clip as temporary motion cues before removal: estimate or proxy the 6DoF / 2D trajectory of the spatula, egg mold, plate contact, and gripper-contact region, then compare raw versus edited clips. Acceptance: choose a minimal tracker stack or proxy metric; produce before/after trajectory plots or overlays for at least one drag-demo clip; report temporal smoothness, contact discontinuity, and object-drift failures; define whether full ComPose-style 6DoF tracking, object-mask tracking, or a lighter keypoint/pose proxy is enough for the first production gate.",
