            "comment_id": "comment_drag_demo_compose_reference_20260527",
            "author": "Boris / Codex",
            "body": "Reference added: ComPose: When to Trust Hands for Object Pose Tracking (arXiv:2605.23523). Main lesson for drag-demo editing: the hand is not only an occluder; under object occlusion it is also a motion cue. The hand-removal pipeline should use raw hand/contact evidence to track manipulated-object motion before deleting hands, then reject edits that hallucinate plausible pixels while breaking spatula / egg-mold / plate contact trajectory or temporal smoothness. Practical first gate can be lighter than full ComPose: object masks + hand/contact keypoints + trajectory overlays, with RTE/RRE/TCC-style metrics if 6DoF estimates become available.",
