            "comment_id": "clawcross_21a1db4d525f",
            "author": "Progress",
            "body": "[2026-05-23] Probe v0 finished. Built 5 heads (qwen_baseline / color_saliency / geom_compact / qwen_filtered / color_x_qwen). Run: .venv/bin/python contact_object_head.py. Robot_still cup IoU: H2 geom_compact 0.810 vs Qwen 0.212 (3.8x lift), precision 1.0, penetration_vs_gt_scene 0.0. Poster silhouette IoU: H2 geom_compact 0.856 vs Qwen 0.514 (1.7x lift), precision 1.0, penetration_vs_gt_scene 0.0. Contact event proxy (touch-within-4px-of-robot): TP=1 FP=0 FN=0 TN=1 across both scenes for all heads — sanity, not discriminating, N=2. Sliding proxy: unmeasurable_single_image (defer to temporal probe). Key reads: (1) color is the strongest feature; (2) Qwen non-base layers alone are worse than nothing (H3 IoU 0.016/0.242, penetration 0.95/0.75 — floods the image); (3) Qwen layers do not add info on top of color (H4 ≈ H2); (4) chained head: robot mask subtraction is essential. Penetration vs Qwen base = 1.0 for every head (uninformative; Qwen base alpha=1 everywhere); replaced with penetration_vs_gt_scene as primary. Artifacts: contact_object_head.py, contact-object-head.md, outputs_contact_object_head/score_summary.json, outputs_contact_object_head/{robot_still,poster}/mask_*.png + overlays. Acceptance: poster+robot_still both produce object/contact mask; contact recall/precision recorded; penetration proxy recorded; sliding marked unmeasurable as expected.",
