            "comment_id": "comment_fracture_soft_wrist_shapeforce_archive_20260605",
            "author": "Boris / Codex",
            "body": "Archive decision from user-provided paper: ShapeForce: Low-Cost Soft Robotic Wrist for Contact-Rich Manipulation (arXiv:2511.19955) directly covers the standalone soft-wrist/contact-feedback route with a low-cost plug-and-play compliant wrist, marker-tracked deformation, force-like signals, and contact-rich manipulation evaluation comparable to six-axis force-torque sensing. Keep ShapeForce as a reference, not a separate active Survey project. The fracture-reassembly half is not solved by ShapeForce, but it should reopen only as an independent benchmark with real objects, simulator/real split, metrics, and owner.",
