            "body": "Research update 2026-06-17: prefer Wan2.1 for first UMI dual-wrist training. Official Wan2.2 docs/model cards describe A14B as a two-expert MoE denoiser: high-noise expert handles early/high-noise/layout steps, low-noise expert handles later/detail steps, with an SNR/timestep switch. Community training reports in DiffSynth-Studio also show practical instability when separately fine-tuning high vs low noise experts; one report says the same task learned better on Wan2.1 than Wan2.2. Wan2.1 has simpler single-backbone training and mature LoRA/full-finetune recipes in VideoX-Fun, finetrainers, DiffSynth-Studio, and diffusion-pipe. Decision: implement Route A concat baseline and Route B dual-latent prototype on Wan2.1 first; keep Wan2.2-A14B for later quality comparison after the schema works, or evaluate Wan2.2-TI2V-5B only if we specifically need its dense 5B unified TI2V path.",
